; Lameboy door — sysop defaults.
;
; Copy to "lameboy.ini" next to the binary and edit. Everything here is
; optional; a command-line flag (--roms, --fps, --ansi-music) overrides the
; matching key. Per-call values (the DOOR32 dropfile path and the user id) are
; NOT configured here — the BBS supplies those on the command line at launch.
;
; Lines starting with ; or # are comments.

; ROM directory. Relative paths are resolved from the door's working directory.
; Default: roms/ beside the binary.
;roms = roms

; Transmit frame-rate cap (clamped to 5-60). Lower it on slow links. Default 20.
;fps = 20

; Offer ANSI-music sound (the caller still picks Off / ANSI / APC in the menu).
; Set false for a silent door / APC-only. Default true.
;ansi_music = true

; --- APC audio streaming (SyncTERM PCM) -------------------------------------
; These tune the real-PCM stream sent to APC-audio terminals. They do nothing
; for Off / ANSI sound. The stream keeps itself in sync with wall-clock on its
; own (speeding up small drift, dropping big stalls), so there is no buffer or
; latency knob to guess at — watch the live "A:" readout in the FPS bar to tune.
;
; Output sample rate in Hz (clamped 5512-44100, snapped to a divisor of 44100).
; This is the bandwidth lever: the audio shares the link with the video, so a
; lower rate clears faster and is the best fix for latency on a slow link. GB
; audio is lo-fi, so 11025 sounds nearly identical to 22050 at half the bytes.
; Default 22050.
;audio_rate = 22050
;
; Smallest clip emitted, in ms (clamped 10-250); also the drop/skip granularity.
; Smaller = subtler skips and tighter timing, at a little more per-clip overhead.
; Default 40.
;audio_chunk_ms = 40
